it succeeded by merging local advocacy with international mobilization. He emphasizes the role played at the grassroots level by women, migrant workers, and other underrepresented groups who were at greatest risk. Environmental groups, for their part, gathered and shared evidence about the harms of at-sea incineration, building scientific consensus and influencing international debates.Smoke on the Water tells the compelling story of a campaign against environmental degradation in which people from marginalized communities took on the might of the U.S. military-industrial complex. It offers new insights into the transnational dimensions of environmental regulation, the significance of nonstate actors in international history, and the making of environmental justice movements.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aEnvironmentalismxHistoryy20th century2DLC. 0aHazardous wastesxIncinerationxEnvironmental aspectsxHistoryy20th century2DLC. 0aHazardous wastesxIncinerationxEnvironmental aspectsxHistoryy20th century. 0aHazardous wastesxIncinerationxEnvironmental aspects. 0aHazardous wastesxIncinerationzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century2DLC. 0aHazardous wastesxIncinerationzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aWaste disposal in the oceanxEnvironmental aspects. 0aWaste disposal in the oceanxGovernment policyzUnited States. 0aWaste disposal in the oceanzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century2DLC. 7aNATURE / Environmental Conservation & Protection.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertColumbia University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311074967008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of 